description:
It's finally time to attempt a Self-Avoiding Walk! In this video, I quickly visualize a simple JavaScript p5.js implementation of a self-avoiding walk. I then tackle the more complex problem of backtracking to find a solution to a space-filling self-avoiding walk. https://thecodingtrain.com/CodingChallenges/162-self-avoiding-walk.html

🕹️ Basic Self Avoiding Walk: https://editor.p5js.org/codingtrain/sketches/2_4gyDD_9
🕹️ Self Avoiding Walk with Backtracking: https://editor.p5js.org/codingtrain/sketches/dRWS3A9nq
🕹️ Self Avoiding Walk 3D: https://editor.p5js.org/codingtrain/sketches/D0ONOlCDT
🕹️ Self Avoiding Walk with Bezier: https://editor.p5js.org/codingtrain/sketches/KFbX0NWgh
🕹️ Self Avoiding Walk with Recursion: https://editor.p5js.org/codingtrain/sketches/UPxBk1YiB
